access</span></a></div></th><td style=\"text-align:left;\">\nyes</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/ISO_4\" title=\"ISO 4\">ISO 4</a></div></th><td class=\"identifier\" style=\"text-align:left;\">\nFind out <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://marcinwrochna.github.io/abbrevIso/?search=Perspectives_on_Terrorism\">here</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background:#dfc;\">Indexing<span class=\"infobox-journal-search\" style=\"display:none;\"><br /><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://miar.ub.edu/issn/2334-3745\">MIAR</a></span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"type\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number\" title=\"International Standard Serial Number\">ISSN</a></span></th><td style=\"text-align:left;\">\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/search?fq=x0:jrnl&amp;q=n2:2334-3745\">2334-3745</a><br /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"type\"><a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a></span></th><td style=\"text-align:left;\">\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/journals/23343745.html\">23343745</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background:#dfc;\">Links</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;text-align:left;\">\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.terrorismanalysts.com/pt/index.php/pot/index\">Journal homepage</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Perspectives on Terrorism</b></i> is an <a href=\"/wiki/Open-source\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Open-source\">open-source</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Peer-reviewed\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Peer-reviewed\">peer-reviewed</a> academic journal covering <a href=\"/wiki/Terrorism\" title=\"Terrorism\">terrorism</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Counter-terrorism\" title=\"Counter-terrorism\">counter-terrorism</a> published jointly by the Terrorism Research Initiative (headquartered in Vienna, Austria) and the Institute of Security and Global Affairs at <a href=\"/wiki/Leiden_University\" title=\"Leiden University\">Leiden University</a>, The Hague, the Netherlands. It was established in 2007 as an alternative to the conventional subscription fee-based journals in the field and continues publication as of 2018, releasing six issues per year. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=James_J._F._Forest&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"James J. F. Forest (page does not exist)\">James J. F. Forest</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts\" title=\"University of Massachusetts\">University of Massachusetts</a>, USA) and <a href=\"/wiki/Alex_P._Schmid\" title=\"Alex P. Schmid\">Alex P. Schmid</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/International_Centre_for_Counter-Terrorism\" title=\"International Centre for Counter-Terrorism\">International Centre for Counter-Terrorism</a>, The Hague) serve as the Editors-in-Chief; Robert Wesley was a founding editor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-welcome_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-welcome-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The journal's editors state that the open-source nature allows exposure of research published in the journal to a broader audience than traditional academic journals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The website receives 100,000 annual visitors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-welcome_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-welcome-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Email subscribers and website visitors discuss its research articles at the journal's <a href=\"/wiki/Twitter\" title=\"Twitter\">Twitter</a> feed.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Abstracting_and_indexing\">Abstracting and indexing</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Perspectives_on_Terrorism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Abstracting and indexing\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The journal has been abstracted and indexed in <a href=\"/wiki/Scopus\" title=\"Scopus\">Scopus</a> since 2017.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> All content is available via <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Perspectives_on_Terrorism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-welcome-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-welcome_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-welcome_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.terrorismanalysts.com/pt/index.php/pot/pages/view/Welcome\"><i>Word of Welcome from the Editors</i></a>, Terrorism Research Initiative<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">, retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">28 May</span> 2018</span></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Word+of+Welcome+from+the+Editors&amp;rft.pub=Terrorism+Research+Initiative&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.terrorismanalysts.com%2Fpt%2Findex.php%2Fpot%2Fpages%2Fview%2FWelcome&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APerspectives+on+Terrorism\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"